An MA thesis is an independent research project that corresponds to the requirements of this guide and demonstrates the student's theoretical and practical knowledge, skills to use particular sources as well as the ability to formulate coherent arguments and express them in writing. An MA thesis is a clear and synthesized research paper where a clear problem statement is outlined and where scientific methods are used to analyze the object of study.
The course is connected with a development seminar that lasts through all four semesters, during which time the students will implement a specific project.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provides knowledge in a (specific) research field along with skills to write an MA thesis paper. Writing an MA thesis is compulsory and the topic of the thesis must be related to the EU.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the course a student will: - plan and implement different acitivities to reach the aims set and play various roles within a group; - find solutions to a variety of theoretical and practical problems; - critically analyze the relevant literature published in English and Estonian, argue to demonstrate personal opinion, draw conclusions and generalize; - analyze the empirical material in selected areas; - fulfill the requirements to a scientific research and acquire competencies to apply various scientific research methods. Key competences to be improved: sense making, novel and adaptive thinking, social intelligence, transdisciplinarity, new media literacy, computional thinking, cognitive loead management, cross-cultural competency, design mindset, virtual collaboration.
